        <mj-text font-family="verdana, Arial" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:700;">Japanese Ship Sails Through Taiwan Strait for First Time</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text font-family="verdana, Arial" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Avenir Next',Avenir,'Helvetica Neue',Helvetica,Ubuntu,Roboto,Noto,'Segoe ui',Arial,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.6;">A Japanese warship, the <a target="_blank" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cm28yd04xxno">JS Sazanami</a>, sailed through the Taiwan Strait for the first time, accompanied by Australian and New Zealand ships. This passage is significant because Japan usually avoids the strait to avoid angering China, and it was part of military exercises in the South China Sea.</p>
          <p style="font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Avenir Next',Avenir,'Helvetica Neue',Helvetica,Ubuntu,Roboto,Noto,'Segoe ui',Arial,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.6;">China, which claims the Taiwan Strait, complained about this. Japan has not given a clear comment or explanation but often cites military discretion and acknowledges growing concerns over China's frequent <a target="_blank" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cr40dpz1rkwo">airspace violations</a>. The Taiwan Strait is a crucial international shipping route, and more countries like the US, Canada, Australia, and Germany have increased patrols to assert freedom of navigation, challenging China's claims. This marks a shift in Japan’s stance, showing increased naval presence in response to China's maritime actions. Two <a target="_blank" href="https://apnews.com/article/germany-china-taiwan-strait-warship-0bc53be4d6dc363c5ef21eedfc721206">German warships</a> also sailed through the straits two weeks ago for the first time in twenty years.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding-top="20px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
